This new evaluation of the n+13C reactions is based on a six-      628 1451
channel R-matrix analysis of reactions in the 14C system at        628 1451
energies up to 20 MeV.  Data included were total cross sections    628 1451
[1,2,3] and angular distributions up to 5 MeV[4,5]. A fair fit is  628 1451
obtained to the 3676 data points included.                         628 1451
                                                                   628 1451
Total (MT=1), elastic (MT=2), inelastic (MT=51,52,53) and alpha    628 1451
production (MT=800) cross sections calculated from the             628 1451
R-matrix parameters of the fit are given in File 3, while          628 1451
Legendre coefficients for the elastic and inelastic angular        628 1451
distributions are given in File 4.                                 628 1451
                                                                   628 1451
Preliminary capture data (MT=102) are included in File 3, based on 628 1451
a 1/v extrapolation of the thermal value of Firestone et al. [6],  628 1451
joined with a smoothed representation of the 14C photoneuton data  628 1451
of Pywell [7] that had been reversed using detailed balance.  An   628 1451
insert describing the narrow 2+ resoance at 154 keV was also       628 1451
added.  However, the evaluated cross section runs well below the   628 1451
data of Shima and of Raman in the 10s of keV region.               628 1451
